<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1318138 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?resize=600%2C600&#038;ssl=1" alt="Three men docked for allegedly robbing lady at toy gunpoint" width="600" height="600" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1 107w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?resize=58%2C58&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?resize=194%2C194&amp;ssl=1 194w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?resize=130%2C130&amp;ssl=1 130w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/gun.jpg?resize=560%2C560&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Three men who allegedly used a tricycle to rob a lady at toy gunpoint, on Friday appeared in an Ebute Meta Chief Magistrates’ Court, in Lagos. Taofeek Adebayo, 24, Amos Marvelous, 21 and Sodiq Suleiman, 18, were arraigned on charges of conspiracy, stealing, and breach of the peace. The defendants, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. The Prosecutor, Insp. Emmanuel Silas told the court that the defendants committed the offences on Jan. 4, at 9:30 p.m., along Funsho Williams Avenue, Alaka, Surulere. Silas alleged that the three men conspired to rob a passenger, Victoria Emedem, and stole her handbag and phones valued at N120, 000, after brandishing a toy gun to scare her. According to him, the defendants often use their tricycle to carry unsuspecting passengers and rob them of their belongings. He said the offences contravened sections 168(d), 287 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos, 2015. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs Adeola Adedayo, ordered remand of the defendants at the Ikoyi Custodial Centre. Adedayo also ordered that a proper bail application should be brought before the court and then fixed Feb 11, for continuation of hearing. Vanguard News Nigeria An Ikeja Magistrates’ Court on Friday remanded a 27- year-old unemployed man, Saliu Alowonle, in Kirikiri Prisons for allegedly robbing and raping a teenage girl at gunpoint. May 19, 2019 In "News" Three men, Emmanuel Oyedepo, Jamiu Shodeinde and Kayode Adewuyi, were Thursday, arraigned before an Ikeja Magistrate's court for allegedly robbing one Adebayo Rachael of his property worth N158, 300. August 22, 2013 In "News" An Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court on Friday remanded a 27-year-old job applicant, Jacob Odili, in the Kirikiri Correctional Centre, for allegedly robbing a man of N70,000 cell phone, with a toy gun. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs O.A. Aderibigbe, who gave the order, did not take the plea of the defendant.… December 13, 2019 In "News"